{"title_page": "Safia Juuko Nalule", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name   = Safia Juuko Nalule\n| image =\n| image_size     = \n| caption  = \n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1966|3|15}}\n| birth_place = [[Uganda]]\n| death_date  = \n| death_place = \n| alma_mater         =[[Makerere University]]<br/> {{small|([[Bachelor's degree]])}}<br/>[[Law Development Centre]]<br /> {{small|([[Dip.Law.Pract]])}}<br/>[[Makerere University]]<br/> {{small|(Master of Arts in Human Rights]])}}\n| occupation     =Legislator \n| years_active              = 1990\u2013present\n| nationality               = Ugandan\n| citizenship               = [[Uganda]]\n| residence                 = [[Uganda]]\n| known_for                 = Politics\n| spouse                    = \n| networth                  = \n| home_town                 = [[Kampala]]\n| title                     = Member of Parliament<br/>[[People with Disabilities|Central Region,Uganda]]\n}}\n\nSafia Juuko Nalule (born 15 [[March]] [[1966]]<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.parliament.go.ug/mp_database/profile.php?mid=316|title=Parliament of Uganda|website=www.parliament.go.ug|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref>) is a Ugandan [[legislator]] currently serving as the elected woman representative for  [[Disability|People with Disabilities]] ,  [[Central Region, Uganda]] in Uganda's tenth parliament. Politically, she is affiliated to the [[National Resistance Movement]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nrm.ug/organ/nrm-parliamentary-caucus|title=NRM Parliamentary Caucus|last=National Resistance Movement|first=|date=1 January 2017|website=National Resistance Movement|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref> under whose ticket she contested in the [[2016 Ugandan general election|2016 general elections]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ec.or.ug/sites/default/files/docs/Gazette%20List%20Elected%20MPs%202016.pdf|title=General Parliamentary Elections 2016 Gazette List|last=Electoral Commission|first=|date=13 April 2016|website=Electoral Commission of Uganda|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref>. However, she has held that position since 2006<ref name=\":0\" />.\n\n== Background and Education ==\nSafia Juuko Nalule obtained a bachelors degree from [[Makerere University]] in [[1990]] and thereafter a Certificate in Business Management Training from the [[International Labour Organization|International Labour Organisation]] / Federation of Uganda Employers in [[1991]]. In [[1996]], she obtained two certificates - Certificate in Leadership for Women from [[Eastern and Southern African Management Institute|ESAMI]] and a Certificate in Leadership and Microfinance Management from Mobility International USA (MIUSA). She followed that up with a [[Diploma in Law]] from the [[Law Development Centre]] in 2006 and later a Master of Arts in [[Human Rights]] from [[Makerere University]] in [[2016]]<ref name=\":0\" />.                                   \n\n== Career ==\nSafia Juuko Nalule has been a legislator since [[2006]] , sitting in the [[List of members of the eighth Parliament of Uganda|eighth]] and [[List of members of the ninth Parliament of Uganda|ninth]] parliaments of Uganda. As of [[2020]], she was named a commissioner on the Parliamentary Commission<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.parliament.go.ug/page/parliamentary-commission|title=Parliamentary Commission|last=child|date=2018-02-27|website=www.parliament.go.ug|language=en|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ugandaradionetwork.com/story/parliament-gets-back-bench-commissioners|title=Parliament Gets Two New Backbench Commissioners|website=Uganda Radio Network|language=en|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref>.\n\nPrior to that, between 2005 and 2006, she served as a [[Commissioner]] with the Constitutional Review Commission under the Ugandan [[Ministry of Justice and Constitutional Affairs (Uganda)|Ministry of Justice and Constitutional Affairs .]] She was also a Councillor with the then Kampala City Council between [[1997]] and [[2006]]. From [[1996]] to 2005, she worked as the [[Executive director|Executive Director]] of [https://disabilityrightsfund.org/grantees/disabled-womens-network-and-resource-organization-in-uganda/ Disabled Women Network and Resource Organisation in Uganda (DWNRO)]  \n\nShe has served as [[board member]] on the [http://nudipu.org/ National Union of Disabled Persons of Uganda (NUDIPU)] from [[2015]] to date ,and for the [[Uganda Women's Network|Uganda Women's Network (UWONET)]] between [[1990]] and [[1997]].                                                                                                        \n\nIn 2017, she was the chairperson of the [[Human Rights]] Committee<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.eoc.go.ug/media-updates/2017/05/human-rights-committee-parliament-meets-equal-opportunities-commission-eoc|title=THE HUMAN RIGHTS COMMITTEE OF PARLIAMENT MEETS THE EQUAL OPPORTUNITIES COMMISSION (EOC) OVER RECOMMENDATIONS MADE IN THE 18TH REPORT OF THE UGANDA HUMAN RIGHTS COMMISSION (UHRC) {{!}} Equal Opportunities Commission Uganda {{!}} Fighting Discrimination and Inequality in all its forms|website=www.eoc.go.ug|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref>.As a female [[legislator]] in the tenth parliament of Uganda, she is a member of [http://uwopa.or.ug/ Uganda Women Parliamentary Association (UWOPA)]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://uwopa.or.ug/content/members-uwopa-10th-parliament|title=Members of UWOPA of 10th Parliament {{!}} Uganda Women Parliament Association|website=uwopa.or.ug|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref> as well as vice chairperson on the Appointments Committee. She is listed as a member of the Committee on [[East African Community]] Affairs<ref name=\":0\" />.\n\n== References ==\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nalule, Safia Juuko}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1966 births]]\n[[Category:Makerere University alumni]]\n[[Category:Women in Uganda]]\n[[Category:Members of the Parliament of Uganda]]\n[[Category:Women members of the Parliament of Uganda]]\n[[Category:National Resistance Movement politicians]]\n[[Category:National Resistance Movement]]\n[[Category:21st-century women politicians]]\n[Category:Wiki Loves Women (Uganda)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name   = Safia Juuko Nalule\n| image =\n| image_size     = \n| caption  = \n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1966|3|15}}\n| birth_place = [[Uganda]]\n| death_date  = \n| death_place = \n| alma_mater         =[[Makerere University]]<br/> {{small|([[Bachelors Degree]])}}<br/>[[Law Development Centre]]<br /> {{small|([[Dip.Law.Pract]])}}<br/>[[Makerere University]]<br/> {{small|(Master of Arts in Human Rights]])}}\n| occupation     =Legislator \n| years_active              = 1990\u2013present\n| nationality               = Ugandan\n| citizenship               = [[Uganda]]\n| residence                 = [[Uganda]]\n| known_for                 = Politics\n| spouse                    = \n| networth                  = \n| home_town                 = [[Kampala]]\n| title                     = Member of Parliament<br/>[[People with Disabilities|Central Region,Uganda]]\n}}\n\nSafia Juuko Nalule (born 15 [[March]] [[1966]]<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.parliament.go.ug/mp_database/profile.php?mid=316|title=Parliament of Uganda|website=www.parliament.go.ug|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref>) is a Ugandan [[legislator]] currently serving as the elected woman representative for  [[Disability|People with Disabilities]] ,  [[Central Region, Uganda]] in Uganda's tenth parliament. Politically, she is affiliated to the [[National Resistance Movement]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nrm.ug/organ/nrm-parliamentary-caucus|title=NRM Parliamentary Caucus|last=National Resistance Movement|first=|date=1 January 2017|website=National Resistance Movement|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref> under whose ticket she contested in the [[2016 Ugandan general election|2016 general elections]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ec.or.ug/sites/default/files/docs/Gazette%20List%20Elected%20MPs%202016.pdf|title=General Parliamentary Elections 2016 Gazette List|last=Electoral Commission|first=|date=13 April 2016|website=Electoral Commission of Uganda|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref>. However, she has held that position since 2006<ref name=\":0\" />.\n\n== Background and Education ==\nSafia Juuko Nalule obtained a bachelors degree from [[Makerere University]] in [[1990]] and thereafter a Certificate in Business Management Training from the [[International Labour Organization|International Labour Organisation]] / Federation of Uganda Employers in [[1991]]. In [[1996]], she obtained two certificates - Certificate in Leadership for Women from [[Eastern and Southern African Management Institute|ESAMI]] and a Certificate in Leadership and Microfinance Management from Mobility International USA (MIUSA). She followed that up with a [[Diploma in Law]] from the [[Law Development Centre]] in 2006 and later a Master of Arts in [[Human Rights]] from [[Makerere University]] in [[2016]]<ref name=\":0\" />.                                   \n\n== Career ==\nSafia Juuko Nalule has been a legislator since [[2006]] , sitting in the [[List of members of the eighth Parliament of Uganda|eighth]] and [[List of members of the ninth Parliament of Uganda|ninth]] parliaments of Uganda. As of [[2020]], she was named a commissioner on the Parliamentary Commission<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.parliament.go.ug/page/parliamentary-commission|title=Parliamentary Commission|last=child|date=2018-02-27|website=www.parliament.go.ug|language=en|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ugandaradionetwork.com/story/parliament-gets-back-bench-commissioners|title=Parliament Gets Two New Backbench Commissioners|website=Uganda Radio Network|language=en|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref>.\n\nPrior to that, between 2005 and 2006, she served as a [[Commissioner]] with the Constitutional Review Commission under the Ugandan [[Ministry of Justice and Constitutional Affairs (Uganda)|Ministry of Justice and Constitutional Affairs .]] She was also a Councillor with the then Kampala City Council between [[1997]] and [[2006]]. From [[1996]] to 2005, she worked as the [[Executive director|Executive Director]] of [https://disabilityrightsfund.org/grantees/disabled-womens-network-and-resource-organization-in-uganda/ Disabled Women Network and Resource Organisation in Uganda (DWNRO)]  \n\nShe has served as [[board member]] on the [http://nudipu.org/ National Union of Disabled Persons of Uganda (NUDIPU)] from [[2015]] to date ,and for the [[Uganda Women's Network|Uganda Women's Network (UWONET)]] between [[1990]] and [[1997]].                                                                                                        \n\nIn 2017, she was the chairperson of the [[Human Rights]] Committee<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.eoc.go.ug/media-updates/2017/05/human-rights-committee-parliament-meets-equal-opportunities-commission-eoc|title=THE HUMAN RIGHTS COMMITTEE OF PARLIAMENT MEETS THE EQUAL OPPORTUNITIES COMMISSION (EOC) OVER RECOMMENDATIONS MADE IN THE 18TH REPORT OF THE UGANDA HUMAN RIGHTS COMMISSION (UHRC) {{!}} Equal Opportunities Commission Uganda {{!}} Fighting Discrimination and Inequality in all its forms|website=www.eoc.go.ug|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref>.As a female [[legislator]] in the tenth parliament of Uganda, she is a member of [http://uwopa.or.ug/ Uganda Women Parliamentary Association (UWOPA)]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://uwopa.or.ug/content/members-uwopa-10th-parliament|title=Members of UWOPA of 10th Parliament {{!}} Uganda Women Parliament Association|website=uwopa.or.ug|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref> as well as vice chairperson on the Appointments Committee. She is listed as a member of the Committee on [[East African Community]] Affairs<ref name=\":0\" />.\n\n== References ==\n\