{"title_page": "Goals Soccer Centers", "text_new": "{{About|the US 5-a-side soccer business|the British 5-a-side soccer business|Goals Soccer Centres}}\n\n{{use mdy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox company\n| type             = \n| name             = Goals Soccer Centers\n| trade_name       = Goals Soccer Centres \n| fate             =\n| parent           = \n| logo             = \n| foundation       = {{start date and age|2017|7|25}}\n| founder          = [[Goals Soccer Centres]]<br>[[City Football Group]]\n| location         = [[United States]]\n| area_served      = {{flat list|\n*[[United States]] \n}}\n| key_people       = \n| revenue          = \n| operating_income = \n| num_employees    = \n| owner            = [[City Football Group]]\n| industry         = [[5-a-side football]]\n| products         = [[5-a-side football]]\n| subsid           = \n| homepage         = {{url|https://www.goals-soccer.com/}}\n}}\n'''Goals Soccer Centres''' is an operator of dedicated [[5-a-side football]] centers based in [[California]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cityfootballgroup.com/our-business/football-business-investments/ |title=Football business investments |work=[[City Football Group]] |accessdate=February 3, 2020 }}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nGoals Soccer Centers originated from [[Goals Soccer Centres|its British namesake]] in 1987 when Keith Rogers, founder of Goals and its previous CEO, opened the world's first 5-a-side football centre in [[Glasgow]], [[Scotland]] under the brand name of Pitz. After subsequent expansion across the [[United Kingdom]], Rogers opened his first two US-based sites in Southgate and Pomona in the mid [[2010s (decade)|2010s]].\n\nOn July 25, 2017, [[City Football Group]] - owners of [[Major League Soccer]] club [[New York City FC]] and [[Premier League]] side [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] - signed a joint venture partnership with the Scottish company to invest capital into the US operations of the company in order to expand across the continent.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ft.com/content/bee74ae4-7125-11e7-aca6-c6bd07df1a3c |title=Manchester City seals US deal with Goals Soccer Centres |work=[[Financial Times]] |date=July 25, 2017 |accessdate=February 3, 2020 }}</ref>\n\nCity Football group acquired the rst of the Company in 2020 and is now sole owner of the business.\n\n== Man City Soccer Academy ==\nAs a result of its links to Manchester City, Goals sites operate Manchester City-branded soccer schools, where children can register to receive coaching from City coaches and learn to play with City tactics.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goals-soccer.com/mancitysocceracademy/ |title=Manchester City Soccer Academy at Goals |work=Goals Soccer Centers |accessdate=February 3, 2020 }}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{City Football Group}}\n\n[[Category:Soccer in the United States]]\n[[Category:Companies based in California]]\n[[Category:City Football Group]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the US 5-a-side soccer business|the British 5-a-side soccer business|Goals Soccer Centres}}\n\n{{use mdy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox company\n| type             = \n| name             = Goals Soccer Centers\n| trade_name       = Goals Soccer Centres \n| fate             =\n| parent           = \n| logo             = \n| foundation       = {{start date and age|2017|7|25}}\n| founder          = [[Goals Soccer Centres]]<br>[[City Football Group]]\n| location         = [[United States]]\n| area_served      = {{flat list|\n*[[United States]] \n}}\n| key_people       = \n| revenue          = \n| operating_income = \n| num_employees    = \n| owner            = [[City Football Group]]\n| industry         = [[5-a-side football]]\n| products         = [[5-a-side football]]\n| subsid           = \n| homepage         = {{url|https://www.goals-soccer.com/}}\n}}\n'''Goals Soccer Centres''' is an operator of dedicated [[5-a-side football]] centers based in [[California]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cityfootballgroup.com/our-business/football-business-investments/ |title=Football business investments |work=[[City Football Group]] |accessdate=February 3, 2020 }}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nGoals Soccer Centers originated from [[Goals Soccer Centres|its British namesake]] in 1987 when Keith Rogers, founder of Goals and its previous CEO, opened the world's first 5-a-side football centre in [[Glasgow]], [[Scotland]] under the brand name of Pitz. After subsequent expansion across the [[United Kingdom]], Rogers opened his first two US-based sites in Southgate and Pomona in the mid [[2010s (decade)|2010s]].\n\nOn July 25, 2017, [[City Football Group]] - owners of [[Major League Soccer]] club [[New York City FC]] and [[Premier League]] side [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] - signed a joint venture partnership with the Scottish company to invest capital into the US operations of the company in order to expand across the continent.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ft.com/content/bee74ae4-7125-11e7-aca6-c6bd07df1a3c |title=Manchester City seals US deal with Goals Soccer Centres |work=[[Financial Times]] |date=July 25, 2017 |accessdate=February 3, 2020 }}</ref> Although Goals doubled their total locations to four by December 2018,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.insider.co.uk/news/goals-soccer-centres-covina-lescott-13728101 |title=Goals Soccer Centres opens its 50th football centre in the US |work=insider.co.uk |date=December 13, 2018 |accessdate=February 3, 2020 }}</ref> further expansion plans were halted when an internal tax audit in the parent company<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-47718157 |title=Goals Soccer Centres admits 'substantial' VAT error |work=[[BBC]] |date=March 27, 2019 |accessdate=February 3, 2020 }}</ref> uncovered evidence of alleged accounts fraud by former owner Rogers.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ft.com/content/a1fb23f2-b4ed-11e9-bec9-fdcab53d6959 |title=Goals Soccer Centres\u2019 former executives accused of fraud |work=[[Financial Times]] |date=August 2, 2019 |accessdate=February 3, 2020 }}</ref> Following investigations, the parent company was sold to rivals [[Soccerworld]] in October 2019,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-scotland-business-50251122 |title=Goals Soccer Centres bought by rival Soccerworld |work=[[BBC]] |date=October 31, 2019 |accessdate=February 3, 2020 }}</ref> Three months later, Goal's stake in the joint venture was sold to partners City Football Group for \u00a35m, giving the soccer organisation full control of the company.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.sky.com/story/manchester-city-owner-scores-with-goals-us-transfer-deal-11925486 |title=Manchester City-owner scores with Goals US transfer deal |work=[[Sky News]] |date=February 3, 2020 |accessdate=February 3, 2020 }}</ref>\n\n== Man City Soccer Academy ==\nAs a result of its links to Manchester City, Goals sites operate Manchester City-branded soccer schools, where children can register to receive coaching from City coaches and learn to play with City tactics.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goals-soccer.com/mancitysocceracademy/ |title=Manchester City Soccer Academy at Goals |work=Goals Soccer Centers |accessdate=February 3, 2020 }}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{City Football Group}}\n\n[[Category:Soccer in the United States]]\n[[Category:Companies based in California]]\n[[Category:City Football Group]]\n", "name_user": "2601:6c2:4004:96a0:21c5:ebab:4f5b:977", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eHistory)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Goals_Soccer_Centers"}
{"title_page": "Lo\u00edza barrio-pueblo", "text_new": "{{short description|A municipality seat in Puerto Rico}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n<!-- Basic info  -------------- -->\n| official_name            = Lo\u00edza barrio-pueblo\n| other_name               =\n| native_name              = <small>Barrio Pueblo Lo\u00edza</small>\n| nickname                 =\n| settlement_type          = Municipality Seat<ref name=\"2010 Census\" />\n| motto                    =\n<!-- images and maps  --------- -->\n| image_skyline            = \n| imagesize                =\n| image_caption            = \n| image_flag               = \n| flag_size                =\n| image_seal               = \n| seal_size                =\n| image_blank_emblem       =\n| blank_emblem_type        =\n| blank_emblem_size        =\n| image_map                = \n| mapsize                  = \n| map_caption              = \n| image_map1               = \n| mapsize1                 = \n| map_caption1             =\n| pushpin_map              = Puerto Rico\n| coordinates              = {{coord|18.432020999999999|-65.8795748|region:US-PR|format=dms|display=inline, title}}\n| coordinates_footnotes    = <ref>{{Gnis|2415595|Lo\u00edza barrio-pueblo }}</ref>\n<!-- Location ---------------- -->\n| subdivision_type1        = [[Commonwealth (U.S. insular area)|Commonwealth]]\n| subdivision_name1        = {{flag|Puerto Rico}}\n| subdivision_type2        = [[List of municipalities in Puerto Rico|Municipality]]\n| subdivision_name2        = {{flagicon image|Loiza Flag.svg}} [[Lo\u00edza, Puerto Rico|Lo\u00edza]]\n<!-- Politics --------------- -->\n| government_footnotes     =\n| government_type          =\n| leader_title             = \n| leader_name              = \n| leader_title1            = \n| leader_name1             =\n| leader_title2            =\n| leader_name2             =\n| established_title        = \n| established_date    