9 Karnataka Legislative Assembly election|Assembly election, 1999]]\n|J. Jayalalithaa\n|1\n|1\n|1.37\n|''No Changes''\n| ! style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Government\n|-\n|2004\n|[[2004 Karnataka Legislative Assembly election|Assembly election, 2004]]\n|J. Jayalalithaa\n|0\n|2\n|0.07\n|{{decrease}} 1\n| ! style=\"background:#FFA07A;\"| Lost\n|-\n|2008\n|[[2008 Karnataka Legislative Assembly election|Assembly election, 2008]]\n|J. Jayalalithaa\n|0\n|7\n|0.03\n|''No Changes''\n| ! style=\"background:#FFA07A;\"| Lost\n|-\n|2013\n|[[2013 Karnataka Legislative Assembly election|Assembly election, 2013]]\n|J. Jayalalithaa\n|0\n|5\n|0.03\n|''No Changes''\n| ! style=\"background:#FFA07A;\"| Lost\n|-\n|2018\n|[[2018 Karnataka Legislative Assembly election|Assembly election, 2018]]\n|[[Edappadi K. Palaniswami]]\n|0\n|3\n|0.01\n|''No Changes''\n| ! style=\"background:#FFA07A;\"| Lost\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Indian General Elections ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Tamil Nadu General Election\n|-\n! width=\"75\"  | Year\n! width=\"200\" | Election\n! width=\"200\" | Party Leader\n! width=\"100\" | Seats Won\n! width=\"100\" | Seats Contested\n! width=\"100\" | Vote (%)\n!Change of Seats\n! width=\"100\" | Result\n|-\n|1977\n|[[1977 Indian general election in Tamil Nadu|General election, 1977]]\n|[[M. G. Ramachandran]]\n|17\n|20\n|30.04\n|{{increase}} 17\n| ! style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Government\n|-\n|1980\n|[[1980 Indian general election in Tamil Nadu|General election, 1980]]\n|M. G. Ramachandran\n|2\n|24\n|25.38\n|{{decrease}} 15\n| ! style=\"background:#FFA07A;\"| Opposition\n|-\n|1984\n|[[1984 Indian general election in Tamil Nadu|General election, 1984]]\n|M. G. Ramachandran\n|12\n|12\n|18.36\n|{{increase}} 10\n| ! style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Government\n|-\n|1989\n|[[1989 Indian general election in Tamil Nadu|General election, 1989]]\n|[[J. Jayalalithaa]]\n|11\n|11\n|17.12\n|{{decrease}} 1\n| ! style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Government\n|-\n|1991\n|[[1991 Indian general 