. R. Nedunchezhiyan]]<br /><small>(1920\u20132000)</small>\n|16 November 1984 \u2013 9 February 1985<br />25 December 1987 \u2013 6 January 1988\n|97 days\n|}\n\n'''[[List of Chief Ministers of Puducherry|Chief Minister of Puducherry]]:'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!S.No\n!Name<br />{{small|(birth\u2013death)}}\n!Tenure\n!Days\n|-\n|1\n|[[Subramanyan Ramaswamy]]<br /><small>(1939\u20132017)</small>\n|6 March 1974 \u2013 28 March 1974<br />2 July 1977 \u2013 12 November 1978\n|520 days\n|}\n\n==List of Deputy Chief Ministers==\n'''[[Deputy Chief Minister of Tamil Nadu]]:'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!S.No\n!Portrait\n!Name<br />{{small|(birth\u2013death)}}\n!Tenure\n!Days\n|-\n|1\n|[[File:O._Panneerselvam.jpg|75px]]\n|[[O. Panneerselvam]]<br /><small>(1951\u2013)</small>\n|21 August 2017 \u2013 ''[[Incumbent]]''\n|{{age in days|2017|08|21}} days\n|}\n\n==List of Leaders of the Opposition==\n'''[[Leader of the Opposition|Leader of the Opposition of Tamil Nadu]]:'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!S.No\n!Portrait\n!Name<br />{{small|(birth\u2013death)}}\n!Tenure\n!Days\n|-\n|1\n|[[File:J_Jayalalithaa.jpg|75px]]\n|[[J. Jayalalithaa]]<br /><small>(1948\u20132016)</small>\n|27 January 1989 \u2013 30 January 1991<br />27 May 2006 \u2013 15 May 2011\n|2547 days\n|-\n|2\n|[[File:O._Panneerselvam.jpg|75px]]\n|[[O. Panneerselvam]]<br /><small>(1951\u2013)</small>\n|19 May 2006 \u2013 26 May 2006\n|{{age in days|2006|5|19|2006|5|26}} days\n|}\n\n==Prominent Members==\n* [[O. Panneerselvam]] - Deputy Chief Minister of Tamil Nadu, '''AIADMK Coordinator''', Former Chief Minister (3 times)\n* [[Edappadi K. Palaniswami]] - Chief Minister of Tamil Nadu, '''AIADMK Joint Coordinator'''\n* [[R. Vaithilingam]] - '''AIADMK Deputy Coordinator''', Former Minister, Member of Parliament (Rajya Sabha)\n* [[K. P. Munusamy]] -  '''AIADMK Deputy Coordinator''', Former Minister\n* [[P. Raveendranath Kumar]] - Member of Parliament (Lok Sabha), Leader of party in Lok Sabha\n* [[A. Navaneethakrishnan]] - Member of Parliament (Rajya Sabha), Leader of party in Rajya Sabha\n\n'''Leaders Since Inception:'''\n* [[E. Madhusudhanan]] - Presidium Chairman, Former Minister \n* [[M. Thambidurai]] - Propaganda Secretary, Former Union Minister, Former Lok Sabha Speaker \n* [[C. Ponnaiyan]] - Founding member of AIADMK, Organisation Secretary, Former Minister \n* [[Panruti S. Ramachandran]] - Organisation Secretary, Former Minister \n* [[K. A. Sengottaiyan]] - Minister for School education \n\n'''Other important Leaders:'''\n* [[C. Sreenivaasan|Dindigul C. Sreenivasan]] - Senior Minister - Forestry Minister \n* [[P. Thangamani]] - Electricity Minister \n* [[S. P. Velumani]] - Municipal Administration Minister\n* [[D. Jayakumar]] - Fisheries Minister, Organisation Secretary, Former assembly Speaker\n\n'''Puducherry AIADMK Unit:'''\n* A. Anbazhagan - M.L.A, Legislative Party leader (Puducherry)\n* Om Sakthi Sekar - Former M.L.A\n\n'''Karnataka AIADMK Unit:'''\n* M. P. Yuvaraj - AIADMK Karnataka Unit Secretary\n* S. D. Kumar - AIADMK Karnataka Unit Joint Secretary\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==References==\n{{refbegin|2}}\n* {{Citation|first= M. L.|last=Ahuja|title=Electoral politics and general elections in India, 1952\u20131998|year=1998|publisher=Mittal Publication |location=New Delhi|isbn=81-7099-711-9|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CFCjniBF9s8C&pg=PA358|ref=Ahuja}}.\n* {{Citation|first= Atul|last=Kohli|title=Democracy and discontent: India's growing crisis of governability|year=1990|publisher=Cambridge University Press|location=Canada|isbn=0-521-39692-1|url=https://books.google.com/?id=Y_jy1S-77c4C&pg=PA174&dq=ADMK#v=onepage&q=ADMK&f=false|ref=Kohli}}.\n* {{Citation|first= Geetha Kamalakshi|last=Mahendra Singh|title=India votes: Lok Sabha & Vidhan Sabha elections 2001\u20132005|year=2006|publisher=Sarup & Sons|location=New Delhi|isbn=81-7625-647-1|url=https://books.google.c